Haaa-ooei!

1437
01:13:37,936 --> 01:13:39,993
Aaah-haha-ha-aayy!

1438
01:13:40,018 --> 01:13:42,664
I'm proud to be
<i>his</i> family!

1439
01:13:42,689 --> 01:13:45,040
Haooo-whoo-hoo!

1440
01:13:45,065 --> 01:13:48,723
Ho-ha-ay!

1441
01:13:57,680 --> 01:13:58,870
Dante?

1442
01:14:00,537 --> 01:14:01,988
Dante!

1443
01:14:04,901 --> 01:14:06,330
It's Dante!

1444
01:14:11,418 --> 01:14:12,608
Haha!

1445
01:14:17,325 --> 01:14:18,889
Imelda!

1446
01:14:19,261 --> 01:14:20,883
Héctor.

1447
01:14:21,200 --> 01:14:22,685
You look good.

1448
01:14:33,778 --> 01:14:35,037
Dante!

1449
01:14:35,062 --> 01:14:37,655
You knew he was my
Papá Héctor the whole time!

1450
01:14:37,680 --> 01:14:39,242
You are a real spirit guide.

1451
01:14:39,267 --> 01:14:42,245
Who's a good spirit guide?
You are!

1452
01:14:53,177 --> 01:14:54,356
Whoa!

1453
01:14:56,647 --> 01:14:57,724
Haha!

1454
01:15:01,656 --> 01:15:02,903
Dante!

1455
01:15:26,856 --> 01:15:28,217
There they are!

1456
01:15:28,242 --> 01:15:30,131
Miguelito! Miguelito!

1457
01:15:34,677 --> 01:15:36,457
Gracias, Dios mio!

1458
01:15:51,060 --> 01:15:52,985
Mijo, I was so worried.

1459
01:15:53,010 --> 01:15:55,346
Thank goodness
we found you in time.

1460
01:15:56,092 --> 01:15:57,622
And you.

1461
01:15:57,647 --> 01:16:00,060
How many times
must I turn you away?

1462
01:16:00,085 --> 01:16:01,091
Imelda...

1463
01:16:01,116 --> 01:16:04,606
I want nothing to do with you.
Not in life, not in death.

1464
01:16:04,631 --> 01:16:08,348
I spent decades protecting
my family from your mistakes.

1465
01:16:08,373 --> 01:16:11,715
He spends five minutes with you,
and I have to fish him out of a sinkhole!

1466
01:16:11,740 --> 01:16:13,461
I wasn't in there 'cause of Héctor.

1467
01:16:13,486 --> 01:16:15,468
He was in there 'cause of me.

1468
01:16:15,493 --> 01:16:18,144
He was just trying to get me home.

1469
01:16:18,169 --> 01:16:19,980
I didn't wanna listen.

1470
01:16:20,005 --> 01:16:21,919
But he was right.

1471
01:16:22,066 --> 01:16:24,640
Nothing is more
important than family.

1472
01:16:26,066 --> 01:16:28,629
I'm ready to accept your blessing.

1473
01:16:28,654 --> 01:16:30,749
And your conditions.

1474
01:16:30,774 --> 01:16:33,425
But first, I need to find de la Cruz.

1475
01:16:33,449 --> 01:16:34,785
To get Héctor's photo.

1476
01:16:34,810 --> 01:16:36,780
- What?
- So he can see Coco again.

1477
01:16:36,805 --> 01:16:38,651
Héctor should be on our ofrenda.

1478
01:16:38,676 --> 01:16:40,215
He's part of our family.

1479
01:16:40,240 --> 01:16:41,735
He left this family.

1480
01:16:41,760 --> 01:16:43,413
He tried to go home to you and Coco.

1481
01:16:43,438 --> 01:16:45,465
But de la Cruz murdered him.

1482
01:16:46,338 --> 01:16:48,118
It's true, Imelda.

1483
01:16:48,567 --> 01:16:50,324
And so what if it's true?

1484
01:16:50,349 --> 01:16:52,660
You leave me alone
with a child to raise,

1485
01:16:52,685 --> 01:16:54,620
and I'm just supposed
to forgive you?

1486
01:16:54,724 --> 01:16:56,005
Imelda, I...

1487
01:16:56,569 --> 01:16:58,021
Héctor?

1488
01:16:58,055 --> 01:16:59,177
Hunh!

1489
01:17:00,900 --> 01:17:02,692
I'm running out of time.

1490
01:17:03,451 --> 01:17:04,857
It's Coco.

1491
01:17:05,445 --> 01:17:07,179
She's forgetting you.

1492
01:17:08,211 --> 01:17:10,456
You don't have to forgive him.

1493
01:17:10,637 --> 01:17:13,551
But we shouldn't forget him.

1494
01:17:15,954 --> 01:17:18,529
I wanted to forget you.

1495
01:17:19,084 --> 01:17:21,125
I wanted Coco
to forget you too, but...

1496
01:17:21,150 --> 01:17:23,540
This is my fault.

1497
01:17:23,767 --> 01:17:25,569
Not yours.

1498
01:17:27,009 --> 01:17:28,880
I'm sorry, Imelda.

1499
01:17:32,982 --> 01:17:34,637
Miguel...

1500
01:17:34,728 --> 01:17:37,098
If we help you get his photo...

1501
01:17:37,141 --> 01:17:38,703
you will return home.

1502
01:17:38,728 --> 01:17:40,283
No more music.

1503
01:17:40,744 --> 01:17:43,817
Family comes first.

1504
01:17:45,767 --> 01:17:49,055
I... I can't forgive you.

1505
01:17:50,980 --> 01:17:53,100
But I will help you.

1506
01:17:54,461 --> 01:17:56,887
So how do we get to
de la Cruz?

1507
01:17:58,158 --> 01:18:00,936
I might know a way.

1508
01:18:51,079 --> 01:18:52,428
Good luck, muchacho.

1509
